HEADWORD: Mediaevalist
<hw>Me`di*ae"val*ist</hw>
<pr>(m⟦emac⟧`d⟦icr⟧*⟦emac⟧"v⟦ait⟧l*⟦icr⟧st)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One
who has a taste for, or is versed in, the history of the Middle Ages;
one in sympathy with the spirit or forms of the Middle Ages.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>medievalist</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

